The paper deals with learning a compatibility function between image and class embeddings in the context of zero-shot classification, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel model that incorporates latent variables, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses a ranking-based objective function, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with natural language processing, as it uses class embeddings, which are often derived from text descriptions, and therefore could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with visual interpretation of results, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
